## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for security.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers security-aware display,
verification state,
restricted/escalated state,
masked output rendering,
and safe failure rendering.

## validation_rules
- security context must resolve
- verification basis must resolve
- trust boundary must resolve
- disclosure scope must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid security context
- invalid verification basis
- invalid trust boundary
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish verification result,
restriction/escalation state,
masking result,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- security runtime scope is explicit
- masking-aware rendering is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
